<P ID="4"><ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Council</ENAMEX> pulls item from agenda
</P>

<P ID="5">Mayor <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rex Luthor</ENAMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Monday</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">night</TIMEX> informed the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Alderwood</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">City Council</ENAMEX> that city staff asked him to remove an item from the agenda.
</P>

<P ID="6">The item was an agreement with the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Alderwood</ENAMEX> Valley Conference of Governments (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">COG</ENAMEX>) to apply for a Community Development Block Grant (CDBG) for a city-wide housing rehabilitation project.
</P>

<P ID="7"><ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Councilwoman Jennie Angel</ENAMEX>, who is heavily involved with the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Alderwood</ENAMEX> Up! housing rehabilitation program, asked about the delay. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Angel</ENAMEX> was concerned that any delays would stop <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">COG</ENAMEX> and the city from being able to obtain CDBG funds.
</P>

<P ID="8"><ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">City</ENAMEX> Manager <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Robert Rockford</ENAMEX> said he asked the mayor to remove the item because he felt there were too many blanks in what was being presented. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rockford</ENAMEX> said he wanted to bring a complete document before <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Council</ENAMEX>, instead of asking members to approve a document without knowing all the facts.
</P>

<P ID="9">"We do have time," said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rockford</ENAMEX>.
</P>

<P ID="10"><ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rockford</ENAMEX> said the application for CDBG funds doesn't have to be submitted until <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">September</TIMEX>.
</P>

<P ID="11"><ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rockford</ENAMEX> said <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">last night</TIMEX> he was scheduled to meet with <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">COG</ENAMEX> representatives <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">today</TIMEX> (<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Tuesday</TIMEX>) to further discuss the issue.
</P>

 


 


