<P ID="15"><ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Alderwood Police</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Chief Ted Mana</ENAMEX> responded to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Torch</ENAMEX>' concerns. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mana</ENAMEX> said he didn't know if there was an increase in activity <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">this past weekend</TIMEX>, but his officers did make a couple of street racing related arrests. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mana</ENAMEX> also said the police department received 15 reports of loud music from <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">8 a.m.</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last Friday</TIMEX> to <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">8 a.m.</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Monday</TIMEX>. The police chief said a majority of the complaints were from <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">9 p.m.</TIMEX> to <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">3 a.m.</TIMEX> on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Friday</TIMEX>.
